# ECD Decision Support Layer – 2-Engineer MVP Build Plan
## Execution Plan for Innovation Challenge Submission

> **Team:** 2 Engineers (Engineer A: ML/Backend, Engineer B: Frontend/Data)
> **Goal:** Shortlisting + strong Demo Day performance
> **Priority order:** Defensibility → Impact demonstration → Polish

---

# Section A – Scope Freeze

## A.1 What WILL Be Built

| # | Component | Owner | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | Multi-domain risk engine (Cognitive, Motor, Socio-Emotional) | Eng A | XGBoost/LightGBM; trained on validated synthetic data |
| 2 | SHAP explainability integration | Eng A | Top-3 plain-language feature contributions per prediction |
| 3 | Probability calibration (Isotonic Regression) | Eng A | ECE ≤ 0.08 target; reliability diagram output |
| 4 | False-negative monitoring logic | Eng A | Threshold asymmetry for High/Critical; FNR logged per run |
| 5 | Developmental trajectory computation | Eng A | Longitudinal coefficient per domain across ≥ 2 time points |
| 6 | Risk transition detection | Eng A | Flags Low→High, Medium→Critical transitions |
| 7 | Cohort-level impact metrics | Eng A | Block/district aggregates: coverage rate, tier distribution |
| 8 | AWW screening form (Streamlit) | Eng B | Domain-by-domain indicator entry; age-band validation |
| 9 | AWW risk result view | Eng B | Tier badge + top-3 SHAP explanations in plain language |
| 10 | Supervisor dashboard (Streamlit) | Eng B | Block-level table: child list, tier, trajectory trend, referral flag |
| 11 | Longitudinal chart view | Eng B | Per-child trajectory line chart across time points |
| 12 | Consent capture screen | Eng B | Consent form with method dropdown; stored in SQLite |
| 13 | Decision trace log | Eng B | Structured log: timestamp, user, child_id, tier, top SHAP value |
| 14 | Offline simulation mode | Eng B | "Offline" toggle disables backend; shows provisional tier from local model |

**Total: 14 components. No additions permitted without explicit scope change approval.**

---

## A.2 What Will Be Simulated (Not Built, But Demo-Ready)

| Component | Simulation Method | Why Acceptable |
|---|---|---|
| Android offline app | Streamlit `offline_mode` toggle; provisional ONNX-equivalent result | Demonstrates offline-first logic without mobile dev overhead |
| Role-based access control | Session state variable in Streamlit (`st.session_state.role = 'AWW'/'Supervisor'`) | No JWT/Keycloak needed for demo; access boundary logic is identical |
| Multi-user concurrent access | Single-user demo instance; narrative describes multi-tenancy | Evaluation judges architecture, not load |
| PHC referral outcome capture | Static JSON fixture with 3 sample PHC outcomes pre-loaded | Demonstrates the feedback loop; no live PHC integration possible |
| Sync conflict resolution | Simulated with a "reconnect" button that reconciles two pre-seeded offline records | Shows logic without real WorkManager implementation |
| CDPO and State dashboards | Read-only pre-generated PDF or static chart | Core eval weight is on AWW and Supervisor experience |

