## Build Phase 5 – Stabilisation & Demo Hardening

### Objectives
- Eliminate all crashes, UI inconsistencies, and data integrity gaps before Demo Day.
- Freeze the codebase. No new features.
- Produce the submission package.

### Both Engineers
1. Full end-to-end demo run: AWW consent → screening → risk result → Supervisor view → trajectory chart → audit trail. Fix all blockers.
2. Data integrity check: all 50 demo children have correct records; no null tiers; all trajectories computed
3. Edge case testing: child with one time point (no trajectory possible — must show graceful message); Low-tier child (no referral widget should appear); offline mode toggle (must not crash)
4. Remove all debug output, `st.write()` test calls, `print()` statements
5. Lock Python dependency versions: generate `requirements.txt` with exact pinned versions
6. Create `README.md`: setup instructions (3 commands to run), data reset instructions, demo walkthrough link
7. Produce submission package (see Section F)

### Deliverables
- Zero-crash end-to-end demo run verified by both engineers independently
- Pinned `requirements.txt`
- `README.md` with setup instructions
- Complete submission package (all artefacts listed in Section F)

### Validation Criteria
- Both engineers independently complete full demo run without assistance
- No crashes on any of the defined edge cases
- App loads from cold start in ≤ 15 seconds on demo machine
- All submission artefacts present and named correctly

